<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-149] Current perf directory has buggy perf tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-149</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The scripts in the current perf directory are buggy and not useful to run any reliable Kafka performance tests. The performance tools that work correctly are -&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ProducerPerformance.scala&lt;br/&gt;
SimpleConsumerPerformance.scala&lt;br/&gt;
ConsumerPerformance.scala&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, the above are in the tools directory. Ideally, a Kafka performance suite should repackage these tools with some sample performance load and output data in csv format that can be graphed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest deleting the perf directory and redoing this cleanly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
